title: foobar2000 Complete Encoder Pack v3
description:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
foobar2000 Complete Encoder Pack v3

Release notes

This pack allows you to use all the encoder presets bundled with foobar2000.

Extract all the files and folders in "Tools.zip" to a folder of your choice.
In my case, I created a "tools" folder directly below the foobar2000 program folder.
The first time you encode a file, foobar2000 will prompt you for the location of the
command line encoder. Just point to the folder where the extracted files reside.

Note that, to use AAC (Apple) or ALAC you DON'T need to install iTunes or QuickTime.
All necessary files are provided. Similarly, you DON'T need to install Winamp in
order to use AAC (Winamp FhG).

Also included is the Microsoft Visual C++ 2008 SP1 Package (vcredist_x86.exe).
This is needed for AAC (Winamp FhG) encoder. if your system already has it,
you don't need to install it. If you're not sure, try to encode using AAC FhG. If
you get an error message, you probably need to install the VC2008 libraries.

You don't need any other files other than the ones provided here.

This pack works on both x86 and x64 systems.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following encoders are provided:

AAC (Apple) - qaac 2.55
AAC (FDK) - fdkaac 0.6.2
AAC (Nero) - Nero AAC Encoder 1.5.4.0
AAC (Winamp FhG) - fhgaacenc 20151011
Apple Lossless - qaac 2.55 / refalac 1.55
FLAC - flac 1.3.1
MP3 (LAME) - LAME 3.99.5
Musepack - MPC Encoder 1.30.0
Ogg Vorbis - OggEnc 2.88
Opus - opusenc 0.1.9
WavPack - WAVPACK 4.75.2
